text: Andrea Šebestová (born March 16, 1978 in Plzeň) is a Czech rhythmic gymnast. Šebestová competed for the Czech Republic in the rhythmic gymnastics individual all-around competition at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta. There she was 28th in the qualification round and did not advance to the semifinal. == References == == External links == * * Category:1978 births Category:Living people Category:Czech rhythmic gymnasts Category:Gymnasts at the 1996 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic gymnasts of the Czech Republic Category:Sportspeople from Plzeň
